Yes it's nice to know that he's here, but I don't want to know who he is.<br>
<br>
If I knew, likely someone told me and likely they told others, and I wouldn't want Bob to leave because people send him tells constantly.<br>
<br>
I like how he has grown as an author and recreated his style through his work.<br>
<br>
I've read and enjoyed all of this Forgotten Realms books, as well as his Daemon Wars series.  His Spearwielder series is targeted more for a younger crowd, and is the only series I don't plan to finish.<br>
<br>
I look forward to reading more of his works, hopefully more written in the Daemon Wars world he created.<br>
<br>
I would read R.A. Salvatore's Star Wars books except I have too much on my plate to get invovled in Star Wars.  I've never read Star Wars.  I prefer to stick with fantasy over Sci Fi, except to finish Orson Scott Card's works with Bean and the end of Bean's life.<br>
<br>
